Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
• 'The Ribbon Factory' DA approved for 10 residential apartments
• 1 x Studio, 7 x 1 bed, 2 x 2 bed
• All apartments 100% pre-sold off the plan
• 100 metres* from Petersham train station
• Ideal for builder/developers to purchase with design documentation and start construction (subject to CC)
• Vendors instructions is to meet the market on auction day if not sold prior

For sale via auction: Tuesday 13th October at 10.30am
Venue: Auction Works - 50 Margaret Street, Sydney

*approximate

CBRE Hotels are delighted to be exclusively appointed to offer for sale the 'Freehold Going Concern' interest in the West Village Hotel, Petersham.

Key investment considerations include:

- Entry-level inner west trading opportunity with exclusive catchment
- Well-balanced revenue streams delivering on average $66,000 per week
- Recent $2 million renovation and refurbishment - excellent condition and nothing to spend
- 8 x gaming machines - no smoking-solution and 63 x gaming machines removed from immediate competitors over the last 24 months
- 21 x accommodation rooms - next to Petersham train station and proximate to RPA Hospital and UNSW
- Expansive three level trading footprint with extensive outdoor areas and small car park
- 696sqm corner site across two separate lots - scope for further redevelopment (STCA)
- Strategically positioned to capitalise on the Parramatta Road Growth Corridor - 27,000 new homes and 50,000 new jobs
- Represents compelling value when measured against recent and comparable pub sales

CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present, 2-10 Crystal Street, Petersham. The property is a service station investment leased to high-quality tenant, 7-Eleven; Australia’s #1 convenience retailer and independent fuel provider. 

The property boasts a commanding corner location with two street frontages along Crystal Street (46 metres*) and Queen Street (38 metres*). 2-10 Crystal Street is positioned on a large land area of 1,178sqm* and is accessible via Crystal Street. The service station has a total of 12 fuel stations, a convenience store and café serving coffee and a range of hot and cold food options.

The property benefits from the following key attributes:

- Leased to high quality tenant 7-Eleven, Australia’s leading independent fuel retailer with over 550 sites nationwide
- High profile corner location along a main road and just metres from Parramatta Road
- Quality investment within a secure asset class
- Net passing income: $263,325 per annum*
- Land area: 1,178sqm*
- Easy accessibility to Sydney’s CBD and Inner West suburbs

2-10 Crystal Street will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 31st March 2020 at 12pm.
